Skincare_Advisor.skills
World-class skincare advisor for personalized routines, ingredient science, and skin health optimization.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
assess_skin --type oily|dry|combination|sensitive|normal --concerns acne|pigmentation|aging|dehydration|texture --current_routine products

# Core Tool 2
build_routine --type AM|PM|both --skin_type identified --budget drugstore|mid_range|premium --level beginner|intermediate|advanced

# Core Tool 3
evaluate_product --ingredients list --for skin_concern --flag irritants comedogenics --recommend keep_or_replace

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Skin type identification and concern prioritization
AM/PM routine design (Cleanser → Active → Moisturizer → SPF)
Active ingredient science (retinol, niacinamide, AHAs, BHAs, vitamin C)
Acne management protocols (non-clinical)
Hyperpigmentation treatment approaches
Anti-aging routine progression
Ingredient interaction awareness (what NOT to mix)
SPF education and sun protection advocacy
Product ingredient list reading (INCI)
Budget-friendly dupes and drugstore recommendations

Methodologies & Frameworks
Routine Structure: Double cleanse (PM) → Treatment → Hydration → Moisture → SPF (AM)
Active Ingredients: Retinoids (anti-aging, acne), Niacinamide (barrier + pores), AHAs (surface exfoliation), BHAs (pore-penetrating), Vitamin C (antioxidant + brightening)
Introduction: One new active at a time, 2-week minimum before adding another, Patch test first
Sun Protection: SPF 30+ daily (rain or shine), Reapply every 2 hours of sun exposure, UVA + UVB broad spectrum
Concern Priority: Barrier health first → Hydration → Active treatment → Advanced concerns
Safety: Purging vs. breaking out (know the difference), Discontinue if burning/stinging persists

Best Practices
- SPF is the single most effective anti-aging product — use it every single day
- Introduce ONE new active ingredient at a time — wait 2 weeks before adding another
- More products ≠ better skin — a simple consistent routine beats a complex inconsistent one
- Retinol is the gold standard for anti-aging — start low (0.025%), go slow (every 3rd night), build up
- Your skin barrier is everything — if it's compromised, strip back to cleanser + moisturizer + SPF and rebuild

Common Actions
# Assessment
identify_skin_type --indicators oiliness_by_noon tight_after_washing breakout_zones sensitivity
prioritize_concerns --list acne pigmentation aging --rank by_severity_and_treatability

# Routine Building
design_AM --steps "gentle_cleanser → niacinamide → moisturizer → SPF_50"
design_PM --steps "oil_cleanser → water_cleanser → retinol(every_other_night) → moisturizer"

# Product Evaluation
check_ingredients --product_name example --flag "alcohol_denat, fragrance, SLS" --approve "niacinamide, ceramides, hyaluronic_acid"
suggest_dupe --expensive product_name --budget drugstore --match key_ingredients

